Document: CollisionObject3D
Path: godot/classes/class_collisionobject3d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties of CollisionObject3D, including collision layers, masks, priority, disable mode, and input picking behavior.

collision_layer (int): The physics layers this CollisionObject3D is in. Collision objects can exist in one or more of 32 different layers. See also collision_mask. Default: 1.
Method: set_collision_layer(value: int)
Method: get_collision_layer()
Note: Object A can detect a contact with object B only if object B is in any of the layers that object A scans. See Collision layers and masks in the documentation for more information.

collision_mask (int): The physics layers this CollisionObject3D scans. Collision objects can scan one or more of 32 different layers. See also collision_layer. Default: 1.
Method: set_collision_mask(value: int)
Method: get_collision_mask()
Note: Object A can detect a contact with object B only if object B is in any of the layers that object A scans. See Collision layers and masks in the documentation for more information.

collision_priority (float): The priority used to solve colliding when occurring penetration. The higher the priority is, the lower the penetration into the object will be. This can for example be used to prevent the player from breaking through the boundaries of a level. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_collision_priority(value: float)
Method: get_collision_priority()

disable_mode (DisableMode): Defines the behavior in physics when Node.process_mode is set to Node.PROCESS_MODE_DISABLED. Default: 0.
Method: set_disable_mode(value: DisableMode)
Method: get_disable_mode()

input_capture_on_drag (bool): If true, the CollisionObject3D will continue to receive input events as the mouse is dragged across its shapes. Default: false.
Method: set_capture_input_on_drag(value: bool)
Method: get_capture_input_on_drag()

input_ray_pickable (bool): If true, this object is pickable. A pickable object can detect the mouse pointer entering/leaving, and if the mouse is inside it, report input events. Requires at least one collision_layer bit to be set. Default: true.
Method: set_ray_pickable(value: bool)
Method: is_ray_pickable()
